        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 5:54PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 554 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Pine Apple, or 18 miles northwest of Greenville,
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Greenville and Pine Apple.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
